data.chText: （因其言行而被基督教会追封的）圣人，圣徒
data.enText: a person that the Christian Church recognizes as being very holy, because of the way they have lived or died

data.chText: 这些孩子都取了圣徒的名字。
data.enText: The children were all named after saints.

data.chText: 圣人般的人（指特别善良、仁爱或有耐性的人）
data.enText: a very good, kind or patient person

data.chText: 能继续和那个男人一起生活，她简直是圣人。
data.enText: She's a saint to go on living with that man.

data.chText: 他的行为就是再有修养的人也难以忍受。
data.enText: His behaviour would try the patience of a saint .

means: (因其言行而被基督教会追封的)圣人
圣人般的人(指特别善良、仁爱或有耐性的人)

tr: model of excellence or perfection of a kind
a person who has died and has been declared a saint by canonization
declare (a dead person) to be a saint
example: After he was shown to have performed a miracle, the priest was canonized

value.boxr_value: The title is usually pronounced /sənt/. 用作头衔时通常读作 /sənt/。

value.def: A saint is someone who has died and been officially recognized and honoured by the Christian church because his or her life was a perfect example of the way Christians should live.

example.ex: Every parish was named after a saint.
example.tran: 每个教区都以某位圣徒的名字命名。

value.tran: (基督教正式追封的)圣徒，圣人

value.def: If you refer to a living person as a saint, you mean that they are extremely kind, patient, and unselfish.

example.ex: My girlfriend is a saint to put up with me.
example.tran: 能够忍受我，我的女朋友真的很有耐心。

value.tran: 至善的人;极有耐心的人;道德高尚的人;圣人般的人
